<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-10-11T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-10-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="434" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">431.12/2¾: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-10-11T11:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 11,
                                        1921—11 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>132. Embassy’s telegrams no. 190, dated October 8, noon, and no. 189
                            October 4, 5 p.m.<note n="31" xml:id="d434fn31">The latter not
                                printed.</note> The Department is now studying decision of Supreme
                                Court<note n="32" xml:id="d434fn32">Decision of the Mexican Supreme
                                Court, Aug. 30, 1921, in the <hi rend="italic">amparo</hi> case of
                                the Texas Co. of Mexico, <ref target="#pg_461">pp. 461</ref>
                                ff.</note> received several days ago, and additional <pb facs="0602" n="506" xml:id="pg_506"/> instructions will be forwarded shortly.
                            Any suggestions which Señor Pani desires to make will be gladly received
                            by Department.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>